{
  "text": "Ursolic acid (UA), a natural pentacyclic triterpenoid carboxylic acid obtained from TCM herbs and edible plants, exhibits potential anticancer effects through multiple mechanisms in various human cancers including HCC [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Our previous studies have showed that UA inhibited growth of HCC cells through AMP-activated protein kinase alpha (AMPK\u03b1)-mediated inhibition of transcription factor Sp1 and epigenetic regulator DNA (cytosine-5-)-methyltransferase 1 (DNMT1) [CITATION_6] . Others found that ursolic acid induced apoptosis in HepG2 HCC cells via activation/phosphorylation of AMPK and glycogen synthase kinase 3 beta (GSK3\u03b2) [CITATION_7] . However, the precise mechanisms of UA in the control of HCC growth remain to be determined.",
